org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.aneka

Class StorageBucket

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.aneka.StorageBucket
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    FTPStorageBucket, S3StorageBucket

    public abstract class StorageBucket
extends java.lang.Object
    Class representing a storage bucket as defined in Aneka API. This enables to easily create the required PropertyGroup to use in the ApplicationSubmissionRequest.metadata. Extend this class to add new storage bucket types. In particular, the methods to be overridden are getPropertyCount() and fillProperty(int, Property). When getArrayOfProperty() is called, the array is filled using a for loop that calls getProperty(int) with increasing index from 0 up to getPropertyCount().
    Author:
    Riccardo Mancini

      • fillProperty

        protected void fillProperty(int index,
                            Property property)
        Fills the given property knowing its index. When overriding this class, do not handle case 0 but just call this method in the default case. E.g. protected void fillProperty(int index, Property property){ switch (index){ case 1: property.setNameProperty("myName"); property.setValue(myValue); break; case 2: ... default: super.fillProperty(index, property); } }
        See Also:
        getArrayOfProperty()
